"title": "5187: taste",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5187",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The act of tasting is used figuratively of experiencing the goodness of God and his word and of a variety of experiences: misery, sin, wisdom, love, death and blessing.</p>\n<h2>The taste of food or drink</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod16:31\">EXO 16:31</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen25:28\">GEN 25:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:4\">GEN 27:4</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:7\">GEN 27:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:9\">GEN 27:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:14\">GEN 27:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:17\">GEN 27:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen27:31\">GEN 27:31</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num11:7-Num11:8\">NUM 11:7–11:8</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam19:34-2Sam19:35\">2SA 19:34–19:35</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John2:9\">JHN 2:9</a></p>\n<h2>Legalistic prohibitions against tasting certain foods are condemned by Paul</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:20-Col2:22\">COL 2:20–2:22</a></strong></p>\n<h2>Taste used figuratively</h2>\n<h3>Of the experience of misery</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job6:6-Job6:7\">JOB 6:6–6:7</a></strong> <em>In his complaint against God, Job compares the unacceptability of his lot to inedible food.</em> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Job27:2\">JOB 27:2</a></p>\n<h3>Of the experience of the goodness of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps34:8\">PSA 34:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:4-Heb6:5\">HEB 6:4–6:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:3\">1PE 2:3</a></p>\n<h3>Of the experience of the goodness of the word of God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps119:103\">PSA 119:103</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ps19:10\">PSA 19:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer15:16\">JER 15:16</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek3:3\">EZK 3:3</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rev10:9-Rev10:10\">REV 10:9–10:10</a></p>\n<h3>Of the experience of sin</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov20:17\">PRO 20:17</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Of the experience of wisdom</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Prov24:13-Prov24:14\">PRO 24:13–24:14</a></strong></p>\n<h3>Of the experience of love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song2:3\">SNG 2:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:11\">SNG 4:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Song4:16\">SNG 4:16</a></p>\n<h3>Of the effectiveness of Christian influence</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt5:13\">MAT 5:13</a></strong> parallel <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:34-Luke14:35\">LUK 14:34–14:35</a></p>\n<h3>Of the experience of death</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb2:9\">HEB 2:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt16:28\">MAT 16:28</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark9:1\">MRK 9:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke9:27\">LUK 9:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/John8:52\">JHN 8:52</a></p>\n<h3>Of the blessings of the kingdom of God</h3>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:24\">LUK 14:24</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke22:29-Luke22:30\">LUK 22:29–22:30</a></p>\n<h2>To determine not to taste food until a task was completed was commonly used as an oath</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam14:24-1Sam14:46\">1SA 14:24–14:46</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Sam3:35\">2SA 3:35</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jonah3:7\">JON 3:7</a>; ; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts23:14\">ACT 23:14</a></p>",
